slug":"event-155","score":15}],"links":[{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"rec4GS8yWh2R4mpdB","label":"part of"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"recjMT68aIzFLh6cQ","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"recZsS2Zu0zIDwqdv","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"rec9qYH7v18mn09Mt","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"reco82mzy0XTzaOgv","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"recsU2ZSdzBvDqzgI","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"rec0rm6yYA4YUQrkh","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"recm3uRahzpZJ7lDk","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"reczL2DzDEB0XnRNv","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"recdm9AlLF01lFAfP","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"recADz5cMmoTWAEzV","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"reczpxRXxOCJguGTz","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recsAWtM801mXxPiJ","target":"recKRsEFLaEueJvei","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recbRIkz1b6a5jTNq","ref":"1Sam.11.1","text":"Then Nahash the Ammonite came up, and encamped against Jabeshgilead: and all the men of Jabesh said unto Nahash, Make a covenant with us, and we will serve thee.","year":-1095},{"id":"rec3UtQGkKdcZepZA","ref":"1Sam.11.2","text":"And Nahash the Ammonite answered them, On this condition will I make a covenant with you, that I may thrust out all your right eyes, and lay it for a reproach upon all Israel.","year":-1095},{"id":"rec3pn3NUysYW0zTZ","ref":"1Sam.11.3","text":"And the elders of Jabesh said unto him, Give us seven days’ respite, that we may send messengers unto all the coasts of Israel: and then, if there be no man to save us, we will come out to thee.","year":-1095},{"id":"recTEJlWu5My1WRt3","ref":"1Sam.11.4","text":"Then came the messengers to Gibeah of Saul, and told the tidings in the ears of the people: and all the people lifted up their voices, and wept.","year":-1095},{"id":"recVSjN8qZVH1X91u","ref":"1Sam.11.5","text":"And, behold, Saul came after the herd out of the field; and Saul said, What aileth the people that they weep? And they told him the tidings of the men of Jabesh.","year":-1095},{"id":"recSoAlGUyyvYZIAL","ref":"1Sam.11.6","text":"And the Spirit of God came upon Saul when he heard those tidings, and his anger was kindled greatly.","year":-1095},{"id":"recaLgloJKP91iPfs","ref":"1Sam.11.7","text":"And he took a yoke of oxen, and hewed them in pieces, and sent them throughout all the coasts of Israel by the hands of messengers, saying, Whosoever cometh not forth after Saul and after Samuel, so shall it be done unto his oxen. And the fear of the LORD fell on the people, and they came out with one consent.","year":-1095},{"id":"rec1PcM8coPsGO9J7","ref":"1Sam.11.8","text":"And when he numbered them in Bezek, the children of Israel were three hundred thousand, and the men of Judah thirty thousand.","year":-1095}]}
